# Multimodal Track Inspection System (Industry-Style YOLO Pipeline)

This project automatically:

1. Downloads a **real rail dataset** (auto by default) and **UrbanSound8K audio dataset**.
2. Converts audio files into spectrogram images.
3. Builds a combined YOLO dataset (`train/val/test`) for rail + audio modalities.
4. Trains YOLO, validates, and evaluates on test split.

## 1) Project Structure

```text
multimodal_track_inspection_system/
  scripts/
    run_pipeline.py
  src/rail_inspection/
    __init__.py
    config.py
    data_io.py
    prepare_data.py
    train.py
    utils.py
  dataset/
    rail5k/                 # your local rail dataset (if already available)
  data/
    raw/                    # downloaded archives and extracted raw datasets
    processed/yolo_multimodal/
      images/{train,val,test}
      labels/{train,val,test}
      data.yaml
  runs/train/               # YOLO training outputs
  requirements.txt
```

## 2) Prerequisites (VS Code)

- Python 3.10+ recommended
- VS Code + Python extension
- (Optional) NVIDIA GPU with proper CUDA setup

## 3) Setup

```bash
python -m venv .venv
```

Windows PowerShell:

```bash
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

## 4) Rail Dataset Auto-Download

By default, the pipeline auto-downloads a public rail dataset archive:

- `Railway Track fault Detection Resized (224x224)` (direct S3 link)

If you already have a local rail dataset, pass `--rail-local-dir`.

## 5) Run Complete Pipeline

```bash
python scripts/run_pipeline.py --epochs 20 --imgsz 640 --batch 16 --device cpu
```

With your own rail source URL override:

```bash
python scripts/run_pipeline.py --rail-url "https://<your-rail-dataset-url>.zip" --rail-local-dir dataset/rail5k --epochs 20 --imgsz 640 --batch 16 --device 0
```

## 6) What Happens Internally

- Rail images/labels are discovered recursively and split into `train/val/test`.
- UrbanSound8K is downloaded from Zenodo and converted into spectrogram images.
- Audio labels are generated as full-image bounding boxes.
- Combined class mapping:
  - `rail_class_*` first
  - then audio classes (`air_conditioner`, `car_horn`, etc.)
- YOLO model trains and evaluates on both validation and test sets.

## 7) Key Outputs

- Dataset config: `data/processed/yolo_multimodal/data.yaml`
- Best model: `runs/train/<run-name>/weights/best.pt`
- Metrics and plots: inside corresponding `runs/train/<run-name>/`

## 8) Recommended Production Enhancements

- Add MLflow/W&B experiment tracking
- Add model registry and versioned dataset snapshots
- Add CI for data-quality checks and smoke training
- Add deployment API (FastAPI + ONNX/TensorRT export)
- Add drift monitoring for rail camera and microphone streams

## 9) Base YOLO checkpoint

Training defaults use **`yolov26n.pt`** as the backbone weights. Place `yolov26n.pt` in the project root (or pass `--model path/to/yolov26n.pt`). Ultralytics will fetch compatible weights from the hub when supported.

## 10) Streamlit Real-Time Detection Dashboard

This project includes a Streamlit UI for:

- Rail-focused preprocessing (CLAHE, bilateral denoise, optional sharpen)
- Composite severity score (confidence + ROI texture + crack-shape cues)
- Image/camera detection and **video frame-by-frame sweep** with stride controls
- Live dashboard and severity analytics
- Critical/warning alerts with optional **Telegram** and **SMTP email** notifications (cooldown throttled)
- GPS map visualization for detections
- Downloadable **CSV**, **JSON**, and **PDF** reports

Run:

```bash
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

Optional secrets for alerts: copy `.streamlit/secrets.toml.example` to `.streamlit/secrets.toml` and fill values.

Default model path used by the app:

- `models/best_colab.pt`

